'''Otsu''' (šĻô, "kinoto") is the second of the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|lt=Ten Heavenly Stems|8=en|ja|ŚćĀŚĻ≤|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}.<ref>https://www.bing.com/ck/a?!&&p=4c9a92862e1b9aabc3b009cfd0a01023a23ad178c0d8269211d19906d318e4d6JmltdHM9MTc0MzAzMzYwMA&ptn=3&ver=2&hsh=4&fclid=3e6f989f-7779-62d7-1cd7-8d247648633d&psq=Kinoto+(%e4%b9%99)&u=a1aHR0cHM6Ly9qaXRlbm9uLmNvbS93b3JkLzUwNTI&ntb=1</ref><ref>https://www.bing.com/ck/a?!&&p=1be7966818ee6798e5c1fdd09171ddb9d95fab26ae826d08015e33742959ef07JmltdHM9MTc0MzAzMzYwMA&ptn=3&ver=2&hsh=4&fclid=3e6f989f-7779-62d7-1cd7-8d247648633d&psq=Kinoto+(%e4%b9%99)&u=a1aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cudGFub3NoaWlqYXBhbmVzZS5jb20vZGljdGlvbmFyeS9lbnRyeV9kZXRhaWxzLmNmbT9lbnRyeV9pZD0xNzI0MA&ntb=1</ref><ref>https://www.bing.com/ck/a?!&&p=4f4babef6238b7c7cd9b5847a6f52b83af1f7888cd92e4da51952307ac659dd0JmltdHM9MTc0MzAzMzYwMA&ptn=3&ver=2&hsh=4&fclid=3e6f989f-7779-62d7-1cd7-8d247648633d&psq=Kinoto+(%e4%b9%99)&u=a1aHR0cHM6Ly9qbGVhcm4ubmV0L2RpY3Rpb25hcnkvJUU0JUI5JTk5LSVFMyU4MSU4RCVFMyU4MSVBRSVFMyU4MSVBOA&ntb=1</ref><ref>https://www.bing.com/ck/a?!&&p=8a1a36e31997673c3990a8a25fe11ee979cd2b1283c0c44659ae224f81bb0656JmltdHM9MTc0MzAzMzYwMA&ptn=3&ver=2&hsh=4&fclid=3e6f989f-7779-62d7-1cd7-8d247648633d&psq=Kinoto+(%e4%b9%99)&u=a1aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cud29yZHNlbnNlLmV1L2tpbm90by8&ntb=1</ref>

According to the {{ill|Yin-Yang Five Elements theory|ja|ťôįťôĹšļĒŤ°ĆŤ™¨|1=Yin-Yang and Wuxing Theory|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, it is assigned to the {{ill|yin|ja|ťôį|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} aspect of the {{ill|Wood (wuxing)|lt=wood element|ja|śú®|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}. Hence, in Japan, it is also referred to as "kinoto" (meaning "younger brother of wood").

== Overview ==
* The origin of the kanji "šĻô" has been subject to various proposals, but no definitive theory has been established.<ref>{{Citation| author=Yu Shengwu| year=1996| title=Jiaguwen Zhilin (ÁĒ≤ť™®śĖáŚ≠óŤ©Āśěó)| location=Beijing| publisher=Zhonghua Book Company| isbn=7-101-01430-5| pages=1178‚Äď80}}</ref> The character is used as a borrowed form to denote the second in the sequence of the Ten Heavenly Stems.
