r|7=Tahta (klasik element)|1=Wood (wuxing)|lt=Wood (śú®)|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Wood (wuxing)|1=Wood (wuxing)|lt=Wood (śú®)|2=uk|3=–Ē–Ķ—Ä–Ķ–≤–ĺ (–Ķ–Ľ–Ķ–ľ–Ķ–Ĺ—ā)|4=id|5=Kayu (Wu Xing)|6=ms|7=Kayu (Wu Xing)|8=bcl|9=Kahoy (wuxing)|10=ca|11=Fusta (wuxing)|12=it|13=Legno (elemento)|14=es|15=Madera (Wu Xing)|16=nl|17=Hout (element)|18=vi|19=MŠĽôc (NgŇ© h√†nh)|20=tr|21=Tahta (klasik element)|22=ta|23=ŗģģŗģįŗģģŗĮć (ŗģöŗĮÄŗģ© ŗģģŗĮÜŗģĮŗĮćŗģĮŗģŅŗģĮŗģ≤ŗĮć)|2=it|3=Legno (elemento)|4=es|5=Madera (Wu Xing)|6=tr|7=Tahta (klasik element)|1=Wood (wuxing)|lt=Wood (śú®)|13=User:Immanuelle/Wood (wuxing)|1=Wood (wuxing)|lt=Wood (śú®)|2=uk|3=–Ē–Ķ—Ä–Ķ–≤–ĺ (–Ķ–Ľ–Ķ–ľ–Ķ–Ĺ—ā)|4=id|5=Kayu (Wu Xing)|6=ms|7=Kayu (Wu Xing)|8=bcl|9=Kahoy (wuxing)|10=ca|11=Fusta (wuxing)|12=it|13=Legno (elemento)|14=es|15=Madera (Wu Xing)|16=nl|17=Hout (element)|18=vi|19=MŠĽôc (NgŇ© h√†nh)|20=tr|21=Tahta (klasik element)|22=ta|23=ŗģģŗģįŗģģŗĮć (ŗģöŗĮÄŗģ© ŗģģŗĮÜŗģĮŗĮćŗģĮŗģŅŗģĮŗģ≤ŗĮć)|2=it|3=Legno (elemento)|4=es|5=Madera (Wu Xing)|6=tr|7=Tahta (klasik element)|1=Wood (wuxing)|lt=Wood (śú®)|qq=}}. Hence, in Japan, it is also referred to as "kinoto" (meaning "younger brother of wood").
== Pronunciations: šĻô (Stem 2) == * Chinese (Pinyin): Y«ź * Korean: Eul (žĚĄ) * Vietnamese: Šļ§t * Japanese: ** On‚Äôyomi: Otsu („Āä„Ā§) ** Elemental: Kinoto („Āć„Āģ„Ā®, śú®„ĀģŚľü ‚Äď ‚ÄúYounger Wood‚ÄĚ)
== Overview == * The origin of the kanji "šĻô" has been subject to various proposals, but no definitive theory has been established.<ref>{{Citation| author=Yu Shengwu| year=1996| title=Jiaguwen Zhilin (ÁĒ≤ť™®śĖáŚ≠óŤ©Āśěó)| location=Beijing| publisher=Zhonghua Book Company| isbn=7-101-01430-5| pages=1178‚Äď80|qq=}}</ref> The character is used as a borrowed form to denote the second in the sequence of the Ten Heavenly Stems. * When the Ten Heavenly Stems are used for Ranking, "Otsu" signifies the second position. It is also used in classification systems, such as "Otsu-type" (šĻôÁ®ģ) or "Otsu-class" (šĻôť°ě). While these terms are simply labels for categories, many mistakenly believe that "Otsu" implies inferiority compared to "Kou" (ÁĒ≤, the first stem). For example, in the classification of [[:en:ShŇćchŇę|shochu]], there are "Kou-class" and "Otsu-class" varieties. To avoid the misconception that "Otsu-class" is inferior, it is often referred to as "honkaku shochu" (śú¨ś†ľÁĄľťÖé), meaning "authentic shochu." * Additionally, expressions like "difficult to determine between Kou and Otsu" (ÁĒ≤šĻôšĽė„ĀĎ„ĀĆ„Āü„ĀĄ) suggest a comparison where "Kou" is perceived as superior and "Otsu" as lesser. In {{ill|calligraphy|ja|śõłťĀď|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/calligraphy|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/calligraphy|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/calligraphy|qq=}} and other disciplines, these terms are used to indicate progress or Ranking in proficiency tests. * Years ending with the digit 5 in the [[:en:Common Era|Common Era]] correspond to the year of "Otsu." The alternate name for such years is "{{ill|Zhanmeng|ja|śóÉŤíô|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Zhanmeng|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Zhanmeng|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Zhanmeng|qq=}}."<ref>{{Cite web |title=Ancient Alternative Names and Explanations for the Heavenly Stems and Earthly Branches |url=https://www.cidianwang.com/shufazuopin/jiaocheng/932596.htm |website=www.cidianwang.com |access-date=2024-03-08|qq=}}</ref> * The opposite counterpart of "Otsu" is {{ill|Kanoe (Śļö)|cdo|Gńēng (tińēng-gńÉng)|fr|Genggan|gan|Śļö|1=Kanoe (Śļö)|lt=Kanoe (Śļö)|2=ja|3=Śļö|4=zh|5=Śļö|hak|K√Ęng (thi√™n-k√īn)|ja|Kanoe|ko|Í≤Ĺ (ž≤úÍįĄ)|vi|Canh (Thi√™n can)|za|Geng (diengan)|zh-min-nan|Ke‚ĀŅ (Thian-kan)|zh-yue|Śļö (Ś§©ŚĻ≤)|zh|Śļö|1=Kanoe (Śļö)|lt=Kanoe (Śļö)|2=ja|3=Śļö|4=zh|5=Śļö|lt=Kanoe (Śļö)|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kanoe (Śļö)|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kanoe (Śļö)|13=User:Immanuelle/Kanoe (Śļö)|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kanoe (Śļö)|13=User:Immanuelle/Kanoe (Śļö)|qq=}}. * The {{ill|lucky direction|ja|śĀĶśĖĻ|3=ś≠≥Śĺ≥Á•ě|1=Toshitoku-shin|lt=Lucky direction|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/lucky direction|13=User:Immanuelle/Toshitoku-shin|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/lucky direction|13=User:Immanuelle/Toshitoku-shin|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/lucky direction|13=User:Immanuelle/Toshitoku-shin|qq=}} (eho) associated with Otsu is slightly west of southwest (255 degrees).
