r|7=Tahta (klasik element)|1=Wood (wuxing)|lt=Wood (śú®)|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Wood (wuxing)|1=Wood (wuxing)|lt=Wood (śú®)|2=uk|3=–Ē–Ķ—Ä–Ķ–≤–ĺ (–Ķ–Ľ–Ķ–ľ–Ķ–Ĺ—ā)|4=id|5=Kayu (Wu Xing)|6=ms|7=Kayu (Wu Xing)|8=bcl|9=Kahoy (wuxing)|10=ca|11=Fusta (wuxing)|12=it|13=Legno (elemento)|14=es|15=Madera (Wu Xing)|16=nl|17=Hout (element)|18=vi|19=MŠĽôc (NgŇ© h√†nh)|20=tr|21=Tahta (klasik element)|22=ta|23=ŗģģŗģįŗģģŗĮć (ŗģöŗĮÄŗģ© ŗģģŗĮÜŗģĮŗĮćŗģĮŗģŅŗģĮŗģ≤ŗĮć)|2=it|3=Legno (elemento)|4=es|5=Madera (Wu Xing)|6=tr|7=Tahta (klasik element)|1=Wood (wuxing)|lt=Wood (śú®)|13=User:Immanuelle/Wood (wuxing)|1=Wood (wuxing)|lt=Wood (śú®)|2=uk|3=–Ē–Ķ—Ä–Ķ–≤–ĺ (–Ķ–Ľ–Ķ–ľ–Ķ–Ĺ—ā)|4=id|5=Kayu (Wu Xing)|6=ms|7=Kayu (Wu Xing)|8=bcl|9=Kahoy (wuxing)|10=ca|11=Fusta (wuxing)|12=it|13=Legno (elemento)|14=es|15=Madera (Wu Xing)|16=nl|17=Hout (element)|18=vi|19=MŠĽôc (NgŇ© h√†nh)|20=tr|21=Tahta (klasik element)|22=ta|23=ŗģģŗģįŗģģŗĮć (ŗģöŗĮÄŗģ© ŗģģŗĮÜŗģĮŗĮćŗģĮŗģŅŗģĮŗģ≤ŗĮć)|2=it|3=Legno (elemento)|4=es|5=Madera (Wu Xing)|6=tr|7=Tahta (klasik element)|1=Wood (wuxing)|lt=Wood (śú®)|qq=}}. Hence, in Japan, it is also referred to as "kinoto" (meaning "younger brother of wood").
==Pronunciation== ==Years of Kinoto (šĻô)== * Chinese (Pinyin): Y«ź * Korean: Eul (žĚĄ) * Vietnamese: Šļ§t * Japanese: ** On‚Äôyomi: Otsu („Āä„Ā§) ** Kunyomi (elemental): Kinoto („Āć„Āģ„Ā®, śú®„ĀģŚľü ‚Äď ‚ÄúYounger Wood‚ÄĚ) ==Months of Kinoto (šĻô)== == Overview == * The origin of the kanji "šĻô" has been subject to various proposals, but no definitive theory has been established.<ref>{{Citation| author=Yu Shengwu| year=1996| title=Jiaguwen Zhilin (ÁĒ≤ť™®śĖáŚ≠óŤ©Āśěó)| location=Beijing| publisher=Zhonghua Book Company| isbn=7-101-01430-5| pages=1178‚Äď80|qq=}}</ref> The character is used as a borrowed form to denote the second in the sequence of the Ten Heavenly Stems. * When the Ten Heavenly Stems are used for Ranking, "Otsu" signifies the second position. It is also used in classification systems, such as "Otsu-type" (šĻôÁ®ģ) or "Otsu-class" (šĻôť°ě). While these terms are simply labels for categories, many mistakenly believe that "Otsu" implies inferiority compared to "Kou" (ÁĒ≤, the first stem). For example, in the classification of [[:en:ShŇćchŇę|shochu]], there are "Kou-class" and "Otsu-class" varieties. To avoid the misconception that "Otsu-class" is inferior, it is often referred to as "honkaku shochu" (śú¨ś†ľÁĄľťÖé), meaning "authentic shochu." * Additionally, expressions like "difficult to determine between Kou and Otsu" (ÁĒ≤šĻôšĽė„ĀĎ„ĀĆ„Āü„ĀĄ) suggest a comparison where "Kou" is perceived as superior and "Otsu" as lesser. In {{ill|calligraphy|ja|śõłťĀď|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/calligraphy|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/calligraphy|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/calligraphy|qq=}} and other disciplines, these terms are used to indicate progress or Ranking in proficiency tests. * Years ending with the digit 5 in the [[:en:Common Era|Common Era]] correspond to the year of "Otsu." The alternate name for such years is "{{ill|Zhanmeng|ja|śóÉŤíô|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Zhanmeng|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Zhanmeng|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Zhanmeng|qq=}}."<ref>{{Cite web |title=Ancient Alternative Names and Explanations for the Heavenly Stems and Earthly Branches |url=https://www.cidianwang.com/shufazuopin/jiaocheng/932596.htm |website=www.cidianwang.com |access-date=2024-03-08|qq=}}</ref> * The opposite counterpart of "Otsu" is {{ill|Kanoe (Śļö)|cdo|Gńēng (tińēng-gńÉng)|fr|Genggan|gan|Śļö|1=Kanoe (Śļö)|lt=Kanoe (Śļö)|2=ja|3=Śļö|4=zh|5=Śļö|hak|K√Ęng (thi√™n-k√īn)|ja|Kanoe|ko|Í≤Ĺ (ž≤úÍįĄ)|vi|Canh (Thi√™n can)|za|Geng (diengan)|zh-min-nan|Ke‚ĀŅ (Thian-kan)|zh-yue|Śļö (Ś§©ŚĻ≤)|zh|Śļö|1=Kanoe (Śļö)|lt=Kanoe (Śļö)|2=ja|3=Śļö|4=zh|5=Śļö|lt=Kanoe (Śļö)|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kanoe (Śļö)|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kanoe (Śļö)|13=User:Immanuelle/Kanoe (Śļö)|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kanoe (Śļö)|13=User:Immanuelle/Kanoe (Śļö)|qq=}}. * The {{ill|lucky direction|ja|śĀĶśĖĻ|3=ś≠≥Śĺ≥Á•ě|1=Toshitoku-shin|lt=Lucky direction|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/lucky direction|13=User:Immanuelle/Toshitoku-shin|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/lucky direction|13=User:Immanuelle/Toshitoku-shin|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/lucky direction|13=User:Immanuelle/Toshitoku-shin|qq=}} (eho) associated with Otsu is slightly west of southwest (255 degrees). ==Days of Kinoto (šĻô)== == Earthly Branches Containing Yi (šĻô) == {{Wiktionary|šĻô|1=Kinoto (šĻô)|lt=Kinoto (šĻô)|2=ja|3=šĻô|4=zh|5=šĻô|1=Kinoto (šĻô)|qq=}} {| class="wikitable alternance droite" |{{ill|Yin Wood Ox|ja|šĻôšłĎ|1=Yin Wood Ox|zh|šĻôšłĎ|1=Yin Wood Ox|ko|žĚĄž∂ē|fr|Buffle de bois|de|Holz-B√ľffel|en|Wood Ox|lt=šĻôšłĎ (Yin Wood Ox)|lt_ko=žĚĄž∂ē|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yin Wood Ox|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yin Wood Ox|13=User:Immanuelle/Yin Wood Ox|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yin Wood Ox|13=User:Immanuelle/Yin Wood Ox|qq=}} |- style="text-align:left;font-size:100%" |{{ill|Yin Wood Pig|ja|1=Yin Wood Pig|2=ja|šĻôšļ•|1=Yin Wood Pig|zh|1=Yin Wood Pig|2=ja|šĻôšļ•|1=Yin Wood Pig|ko|žĚĄŪēī|fr|Cochon de bois|de|Holz-Schwein|en|Wood Pig|lt=šĻôšļ• (Yin Wood Pig)|lt_ko=žĚĄŪēī|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yin Wood Pig|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yin Wood Pig|13=User:Immanuelle/Yin Wood Pig|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yin Wood Pig|13=User:Immanuelle/Yin Wood Pig|qq=}} |- style="text-align:left;font-size:100%" |{{ill|Yin Wood Rooster|ja|1=Yin Wood Rooster|2=ja|šĻôťÖČ|1=Yin Wood Rooster|zh|1=Yin Wood Rooster|2=ja|šĻôťÖČ|1=Yin Wood Rooster|ko|žĚĄžú†|fr|Coq de bois|de|Holz-Hahn|en|Wood Rooster|lt=šĻôťÖČ (Yin Wood Rooster)|lt_ko=žĚĄžú†|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yin Wood Rooster|13=User:Immanuelle/Yin Wood Rooster|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yin Wood Rooster|13=User:Immanuelle/Yin Wood Rooster|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yin Wood Rooster|13=User:Immanuelle/Yin Wood Rooster|qq=}} |- style="text-align:left;font-size:100%" |{{ill|Yin Wood Goat|ja|1=Yin Wood Goat|2=ja|šĻôśú™|zh|1=Yin Wood Goat|2=ja|šĻôśú™|ko|žĚĄŽĮł|fr|Ch√®vre de bois|de|Holz-Schaf|en|Wood Goat|lt=šĻôśú™ (Yin Wood Goat)|lt_ko=žĚĄŽĮł|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yin Wood Goat|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yin Wood Goat|13=User:Immanuelle/Yin Wood Goat|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yin Wood Goat|13=User:Immanuelle/Yin Wood Goat|qq=}} |- style="text-align:left;font-size:100%" |{{ill|Yin Wood Snake|ja|1=Yin Wood Snake|2=ja|šĻôŚ∑≥|zh|1=Yin Wood Snake|2=ja|šĻôŚ∑≥|ko|žĚĄžā¨|fr|Serpent de bois|de|Holz-Schlange|en|Wood Snake|lt=šĻôŚ∑≥ (Yin Wood Snake)|lt_ko=žĚĄžā¨|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yin Wood Snake|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yin Wood Snake|13=User:Immanuelle/Yin Wood Snake|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yin Wood Snake|13=User:Immanuelle/Yin Wood Snake|qq=}} |- style="text-align:left;font-size:100%" |{{ill|Yin Wood Rabbit|ja|1=Yin Wood Rabbit|2=ja|šĻôŚćĮ|zh|1=Yin Wood Rabbit|2=ja|šĻôŚćĮ|ko|žĚĄŽ¨ė|fr|Li√®vre de bois|de|Holz-Hase|en|Wood Rabbit|lt=šĻôŚćĮ (Yin Wood Rabbit)|lt_ko=žĚĄŽ¨ė|qq=|qq=draft|12=simp